  "eventMetadata": {
    "context_description": "Amid ongoing US military actions against Iran—including airstrikes since late February 2026 and recent Strait of Hormuz blockades—Congress has not issued a formal declaration of war or new authorization for use of military force, relying instead on executive authority and prior AUMFs. A two-week ceasefire mediated by Pakistan expired around April 22 after talks in Islamabad collapsed on April 12, prompting renewed escalation rhetoric from both sides. The House rejected a war powers resolution on April 16 to limit operations. A May 1 congressional deadline looms, potentially requiring explicit approval to sustain hostilities, though historical patterns show reluctance for formal declarations in modern conflicts. US-Iran nuclear and sanctions talks remain stalled.",
    "context_requires_regen": true,
    "context_updated_at": "2026-04-27T06:46:50.242Z"
  }
